      <h1><a href="/" style="text-decoration:none;">CSS by Example</a>: properties</h1>
      <hr />
      <p>CSS properties are declared by name in a stylesheet, or inline on HTML elements directly.</p>

<p>Properties are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>plain english words</li>
  <li>hyphenated</li>
  <li>all lowercase</li>
</ul>

<p>Some examples of common properties include <span class="t-highlight">display</span>, <span class="t-highlight">font-size</span>, <span class="t-highlight">width</span>, etc. We will cover these properties by category later on.</p>

<p>Aside from global keyword values, the values you declare for a property are - generally - specific to that property. What that means is that values that work for one property are not guaranteed to work with other properties.</p>

<p>For example, when declaring values for the <span class="t-highlight">display</span> property, valid values include <span class="t-highlight">block</span>, <span class="t-highlight">inline-block</span>, <span class="t-highlight">flex</span>, etc.</p>

<p>The same values would have no effect for the property <span class="t-highlight">width</span>.</p>

<p>Here's a more detailed example:</p>

<div class="codeblock-container">
<span class="codeblock-line"><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>style<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* valid values for dimension properties */</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;body {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;width: 100%;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;height: 90vh;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* valid values for color properties */</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;p {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color: red;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;a {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color: #0099;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;h2 {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color: rgb(172, 23, 45);</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* valid values for layout properties */</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;section {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;display: inline-block;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;text-align: left;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* these values have no effect for these properties */</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;p {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;width: blue;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;margin: #000;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;display: left;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;text-align: inline-block;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-line"><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>style<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
</div>


<p>Oh but wait, there are some global keyword values that are valid to use for every property, such as <span class="t-highlight">inherit</span>, and <span class="t-highlight">initial</span>. More on this later.</p>

<p>Annoying, right?</p>

<p>Also please be aware that CSS values that do not affect the property they are declared for will fail silently and the property value will fallback to a browser default, or nothing.</p>

<p>When declaring properties, some properties may only have effect on HTML elements with specific rendering behavior, or elements with specific layout attribute declarations.</p>

<p>For example, dimension-specific properties like <span class="t-highlight">min-height</span> and <span class="t-highlight">width</span> will only affect box elements. The layout properties <span class="t-highlight">top</span> and <span class="t-highlight">left</span> will only have an effect on box elements with the CSS property <span class="t-highlight">position</span> set to <span class="t-highlight">absolute</span> or <span class="t-highlight">fixed</span>.</p>

<div class="codeblock-container">
<span class="codeblock-line"><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>html<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>head<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>style<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* example of properties declared on the HTML body */</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;body {</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color: red;</span>
<span class="codeblock-text">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>style<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>head<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>body<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#60;!-- inline styles --&#62;</span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#60;!-- won't have any affect --&#62;</span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>div&nbsp;<span class="codetag-attr">style</span><span class="codetag-content">=</span><span class="codetag-value">"right:25px;top:50px;"</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span><span class="codetag-content">Some content</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>div<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>span&nbsp;<span class="codetag-attr">style</span><span class="codetag-content">=</span><span class="codetag-value">"min-height:50px;min-width:100px;"</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span><span class="codetag-content">Some text</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>span<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-comment">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#60;!-- will have an affect --&#62;</span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>div&nbsp;<span class="codetag-attr">style</span><span class="codetag-content">=</span><span class="codetag-value">"position:absolute;right:25px;top:50px;"</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span><span class="codetag-content">Some content</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>div<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span>p&nbsp;<span class="codetag-attr">style</span><span class="codetag-content">=</span><span class="codetag-value">"min-height:50px;min-width:100px;"</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span><span class="codetag-content">Some text</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>p<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>body<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-line"><span class="codetag-caret">&#60;</span><span class="codetag-caret">&#47;</span>html<span class="codetag-caret">&#62;</span></span>
<span class="codeblock-text"></span>
</div>


<p>More on this later.</p>

For a comprehensive list of CSS properties available in browsers, <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference#index">check out this MDN article</a>.

